<div class="main-container">
    <section class="showBullets">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-sm-10 col-md-8">

                    <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

                    <div class="container">
                        <div class="row">

                        </div>
                        <br />

                        <div class="row">
                            <h3>ASP.NET MVC's Folder and Files</h3>
                            <div class="container">
                                <h4>App_Data</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Where data (.mdf) files are stored</li>
                                </ul>

                                <h4>App_Start</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Called when program is started.</li>
                                    <li>RouteConfig.cs – configuration of our Routing rules.</li>
                                    <li>BundleConfig.cs - where we define bundles of client site assets.  For ex, we can combine multiple JS or CSS files.  Reduces the num of HTTP requests.</li>
                                    <li>WebApiConfig.cs – configs for Data Services.  For ex, this file contains the default routing rules and configs for changing property names for results from Pascal to camel notation.</li>
                                </ul>

                                <h4>Content</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Contains the CSS files, images, and any other client site assets</li>
                                </ul>

                                <h4>Controllers</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>AccountController.css = included by default.  Used for signing up, logging in, and logging out.</li>
                                    <li>HomeController.cs = included by default.  Represents the Home page.</li>
                                    <li>ManageController.cs = included by default.  Used for managing user profiles.  For ex, for changing passwords, user authentication, social logins.</li>
                                    <li>/API/folder = holds API controllers</li>
                                </ul>

                                <h4>Dtos</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>user made when creating Dto Controllers for Data Services</li>
                                </ul>

                                <h4>fonts</h4>

                                <h4>Migrations</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>User made when enabling migrations from the Package Manager.</li>
                                    <li>Configuration.cs</li>
                                </ul>

                                <h4>Models</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Domain classes here</li>
                                </ul>

                                <h4>Scripts</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>DataTables (gets created when you install the DataTables package, which is used to easily use pagination, sorting, and other stuff)</li>
                                    <li>JS, JQuery, BootStrap, and BootBox scripts in .js format</li>
                                </ul>

                                <h4>ViewModels</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>User made</li>
                                    <li>Includes View Models (for ex, RandomMovieViewModel.cs)</li>
                                </ul>

                                <h4>Views</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Account = included by default.  Views are named after controllers in the application.  For ex, AccountController.cs corresponds to this Account folder.</li>
                                    <li>Home = included by default.</li>
                                    <li>Manage = included by default.</li>
                                    <li>Shared = included by default.  Contains views that can be used across different controllers</li>
                                </ul>

                                <h4>favicon.ico</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Image of the website</li>
                                </ul>

                                <h4>Global.asax</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Global.asax.cs = tells the program what to run.  It registers stuff.  For ex, the Routes and WebApiConfig, which is used to start the web API stuff.</li>
                                </ul>

                                <h4>packages.config</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Manages the dependencies of our application.  Downloads, installs, and updates packages.</li>
                                </ul>

                                <h4>Startup.cs</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>New approach Windows will take in the future, called ASP.NET Core 1.0, to start the application.</li>
                                </ul>

                                <h4>Web.Config</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>XML that includes the configurations of our application.</li>
                                    <li>connectionsStrings = specifies the DB connection strings</li>
                                    <li>appSettings = specifies configuration settings for our application</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <br />

                        <div class="row">
                            <h3>DB Connections</h3>
                            <div class="container">
                                <h4>.NET MVC Web.config:</h4>
                                <pre><code class="language">
&lt;configuration&gt;
	&lt;connectionStrings&gt;
		&lt;add name="DefaultConnection" connectionString="Data Source=...etc…” providerName="System.Data.SqlClient" /&gt;
                                </code></pre>
                                <br />

                                <h4>.NET MVC Web.Release.config:</h4>
                                <pre><code class="language">
    &lt;connectionStrings&gt;
      &lt;add name="DefaultConnection"
        connectionString="Server=...;Database=...;User ID=...;Password=..."
        xdt:Transform="SetAttributes" xdt:Locator="Match(name)"/&gt;
    &lt;/connectionStrings&gt;
                                </code></pre>
                                <br />

                                <h4>.NET Core:</h4>
                                <p>appsettings.json</p>
                                <br />
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <br />

                        <div class="row">
                            <h3>Secret Info using Keys</h3>
                            <div class="container">
                                <h4>.NET MVC</h4>
                                <pre><code class="language">
&lt;configuration&gt;
	&lt;appSettings&gt;
		&lt;add key="...My Private Key..." value="...my secret here..." /&gt;
                                </code></pre>
                                <br />

                                <h4>.NET Core</h4>
                                <p>appsettings.json</p>
                                <br />

                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <br />

                        <div class="row">
                            <h3>Error Redirect</h3>
                            <div class="container">
                                <h4>.NET MVC</h4>
                                <pre><code class="language">
&lt;system.web&gt;
	&lt;!--&lt;customErrors mode="On" /&gt;--&gt;
	&lt;customErrors defaultRedirect="Error/Sorry" mode="On"&gt;&lt;!--Off--&gt;
		&lt;!--&lt;error statusCode="404" redirect="~/ErrorHandler/NotFound"/&gt;
		&lt;error statusCode="500" redirect="InternalError.htm"/&gt;--&gt;
	&lt;/customErrors&gt;
		
	&lt;sessionState mode="InProc"&gt;&lt;/sessionState&gt;
                                </code></pre>
                                <br />

                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <br />

                        <div class="row">
                            <h3>Mail SMTP</h3>
                            <div class="container">
                                <h4>.NET MVC</h4>
                                <pre><code class="language">
&lt;system.net&gt;
	&lt;mailSettings&gt;
		&lt;smtp&gt;
			&lt;network host="mail.domain.com" userName="theEmail@theDomain.com" port="someNumber" password="your Password here" /&gt;
		&lt;/smtp&gt;
	&lt;/mailSettings&gt;
&lt;/system.net&gt;
                                </code></pre>
                                <br />

                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <br />

                        <div class="row">
                            <h3>Route Configs</h3>
                            <div class="container">
                                <h4>.NET MVC</h4>
                                <p>App_Start\RouteConfig.cs</p>
                                <br />

                                <h4>.NET Core</h4>
                                <p>Through the action attributes</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <br />

                        <div class="row">
                            <h3>Social Media Login</h3>
                            <div class="container">
                                <h4>.NET MVC</h4>
                                <p>App_Start\Startup.Auth.cs</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Uses the IAppbuilder to set the key and password (id and secret).</li>
                                </ul>
                                <br />

                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <br />

                        <div class="row">
                            <h3>HostGator</h3>
                            <div class="container">
                                <h4>.NET MVC Web.config</h4>
                                <pre><code class="language">
&lt;!--  HostGator told me to remove this section:
&lt;system.codedom&gt;
	&lt;compilers&gt;
		&lt;compiler ...etc... /&gt;
		&lt;compiler ...etc... /&gt;
	&lt;/compilers&gt;
&lt;/system.codedom&gt;-→
                                </code></pre>
                                <br />

                                <h4>.NET MVC Web.Release.config</h4>
                                <pre><code class="language">
&lt;system.web&gt;
    &lt;machineKey xdt:Transform="Insert" validationKey="...some 128 character string..." decryptionKey="...some 48 character string..." validation="SHA1" decryption="Auto" /&gt;
                                </code></pre>

                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <br />

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
    </section>
</div>